outlet 13-06-2012 05 21 pm enlarge picture of supplies need 31 completed wings on my fairy sculpt 13-06-2012 05 23 pm learn to sculpt hands there are dozens of_methods to sculpt_hands this is one of the_easiest and_can be modified in scale_up and_down fairly easily this pair of_hands is sculpted in th scale hands are difficult to sculpt accurately because people are intimately aware of_how hands look their shape size proportions etc another reason why hands are difficult to sculpt is mushy clay it is best to use a_firm clay to sculpt hands in order to keep the fingers from_wilting and to prevent you from accidentally mushing the details study pictures of_hands your own_hands and look at the hands other sculptors produce then practice practice practice good way to practice is to buy some gray clay of_your favorite_brand and make hands bake the first_pair and_put them away then_make dozen or pairs kneading them up when you are done every dozen or pairs you sculpt compare them to the first pair you_made and_baked this will help motivate you because you will be able to see yourself improve flatten the balls into ovals the ovals should be about half the size of_the figures_face and_be slightly wider on one end enlarge picture of_flattened balls into ovals the narrow end will be the wrist the wider end will be the hands enlarge picture showing the wrist hand ends pinch and_twist the corners on the wide end into gently tapered cones these are the pinky_and index fingers compare them to each_other enlarge picture showing the pinky index fingers pinch some clay off of_the wrist_end and_roll it into tapered cones that will become the middle_and ring fingers enlarge picture showing how to make remaining fingers the clay gets warm from the friction of working it the heat from your hands etc as your hands get stronger from working with clay recommend that everyone switch to a_firmer clay that is less likely to get_mushy and_wilted like fimo classic place the fingers on the back of_the hand enlarge picture showing how to attach_fingers blend the fingers into the back of_the hand using gentle stroking motions the convex side of_any spoon shaped tool will work for smoothing enlarge picture showing how to blend the fingers turn the hands_over and_blend the fingers into the palm of_the hand enlarge picture showing how to blend into the palms the clay is probably getting_warm and_is easily dentable now be careful spatula tool blend the clay in between the fingers to hide the seams 10 smoothing out the seams can deform the hands reshape the palms now if you need to enlarge picture on how to smooth fingers 11 check the fingers to ensure that they are in proportion to each_other if fingers are too long or too thick take your hobby_knife and_trim bit off the ends roll and_twist the tip back into shape how you handle the clay with out it sticking to the_board the board use there in the image is large ceramic cutting board very light dusting of_talcum powder will deter any sticking but be careful because it will also impede the clay sticking to_itself and_blending when you need it to 12 compare them against one another to ensure that the palm_and fingers are the same length width and_thickness enlarge picture showing_finger and hand comparisons be sure to make a_left and_a right hand not two lefts or two rights for the next step 13 pinch some clay off of_the wrist_end and_roll it into blunt cone attach it near the base of_the palm blend the thumb into the_palm and_the side of_the hand in the same manner you blended the other fingers reshape the hands if you deform them during the blending process enlarge picture showing how to create the thumbs for those having trouble with the clay becoming too warm try using a_can of compressed air the sort used for cleaning off electronics if you turn the can upside_down and_spray the refrigerant comes out if you spray your clay with this only a_bit and_quickly you can cool the_clay and_harden it somewhat -- making your sculpting easier the clay will return to natural state as it warms up the longer you spray the colder it gets be quick just hit it again if needed 14 take your needle tool gently draw the fingernails into the tips of_the fingers there is no shortcut for doing this forget it have looked for_cheats and_shortcuts for years and_have never found one that actually worked without creating more problems like squished clay fingers enlarge picture showing how to create fingernails 15 primp the fingertips to make them tip up towards the fingernail correct the fingernails if you distorted the details usually use a_needle tool to scribe the lines in the palm of the_hand and_along the underside of_the fingers it is easy to go_overboard and_make pruny hands instead of_pretty smooth hands moderation is the key use you own hand as a_reference enlarge picture on final steps 13-06-2012 05 25 pm 10
